### ===========================================
### Customer API — IntelliJ HTTP Tests
### Abschlussprojekt
### ===========================================

@host = http://localhost:8080
@app = final-project-solution

### Alle Kunden
GET {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers
Accept: application/json

### Einzelner Kunde
GET {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers/1
Accept: application/json

### Kunde nicht vorhanden — 404 (nur wenn ExceptionMapper implementiert!)
GET {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers/9999
Accept: application/json

### Neuer Kunde — 201
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Fritz Mustermann",
  "email": "fritz@example.com",
  "phone": "+43 664 9999999",
  "company": "TestAG"
}

### Duplikat Email — 409 (nur wenn ExceptionMapper implementiert!)
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Anna Doppelt",
  "email": "anna@example.com",
  "phone": "+43 664 1111111",
  "company": "TestAG"
}

### Ungueltige Telefonnummer — 400 (nur wenn @Pattern im Model gesetzt!)
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Phone",
  "email": "badphone@example.com",
  "phone": "12345"
}

### Leerer Name — 400
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Ungueltige Email — 400
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Email",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}

### Kunde aktualisieren
PUT {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Anna Meier-Schmidt",
  "email": "anna.updated@example.com",
  "company": "CGS IT Solutions"
}

### Kunde loeschen — 204
DELETE {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers/5

### Nochmal loeschen — 404
DELETE {{host}}/{{app}}/api/customers/5
